1 WHEREAS, 13 people die each day because the organs they need are
2 not donated in time; and
3 WHEREAS, more than 49,000 organ transplants from 23,788 donors
4 brought new life to patients and their families in 2025; and
5 WHEREAS, more than 2,200 children under the age of 18 are on the
6 national transplant waiting list; and
7 WHEREAS, more than 1,874 children were saved by the generosity
8 of donors and donor families in 2025; and
9 WHEREAS, LifeShare of Oklahoma, the nonprofit organ procurement
10 organization, which is dedicated to the recovery of organs and
11 tissue for transplantation therapy in Oklahoma, with a mission to
12 honor donors and save lives through organ and tissue donation; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2003, the first National Donate Life Month campaign
14 was launched. National Donate Life Month takes place in April and
15 features an entire month of activities to encourage Americans to
16 register as organ, eye, and tissue donors and to honor those who
17 have saved lives through the gift of donation.
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
19 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
20 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives supports the
21 recognition of the month of April 2026 as National Donate Life Month
22 and encourages all residents to consider giving life through organ
23 donation and to register with Oklahoma’s organ and tissue donor
